HEADWORD: Imparidigitate
<hw>Im*par`i*dig"i*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impar</ets> unequal + <ets>digitus</ets> finger.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Having an odd number of fingers or toes, either
one, three, or five, as in the horse, tapir, rhinoceros, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Imparipinnate</ent>⟦br⟧
